        | | B14 The Sunday Times Sunday, August 9, 2020 OUR SINGAPORE, WITH LOVE PH OTOS: THE STR AITS TIMES, THE NE W PAPER, BERITA HARIAN, NE W NATION A walk down memory lane Children from childcare centre KinderCorn­er celebrate National Day by putting candles on a red-and-white cake. A Singapore Airlines stewardess steals a last glance at the mirror just before the start of the National Day Parade. 1999: 1976: This year’s National Day may be unlike any other, but whether it’s watching the parade on television or catching fıreworks at the Merlion Park, Singaporea­ns have always found their own unique ways to mark the occasion.
Here’s a look at some highlights of previous years’ National
Day Parades and how families, students and the community have celebrated this special day over the past 55 years. Mr Safrizan Roslan and Ms Siti Noraisyah Mohd Sanusi (centre, both in white) share their nuptial celebratio­ns with Mr Safrizan’s brother, Mr Syazwan Roslan, who married Ms Mahirah Mohd Helmi (background, both in red), on Aug 9. 2015: Madam Sally Chng (foreground) and her friends, dressed as Samsui women, lead the Senior Citizens’ Executive Committee contingent during a rehearsal for a mini National Day Parade near Block 8 Marine Terrace. 2015: Offıcers from the Singapore Armed Forces (SAF) Military Police Command, Singapore Police and Singapore Civil Defence Force (SCDF) perform a thrilling motorbike manoeuvre during the National Day Parade. 2012: Fuhua Secondary School set a record for the most number of people bouncing ping pong balls off the ground with their hands for three minutes as part of their celebratio­ns. To celebrate Singapore’s 44th birthday, Yew Tee Estate displays environmen­tally-friendly National Day decoration­s made out of recyclable materials. Children from Tiong Bahru Constituen­cy Children’s Club don fancy cartoon masks at the National Day Parade at Lower Delta Road. Taxi driver Abdul Rahman decks his taxi out with almost 100 mini Singapore flags and flag decals as a mark of gratitude to the nation. 2010: 2009: 1979: 2009: PRINTED AND DISTRIBUTE­D BY PRESSREADE­R PressReade­r.com +1 604 278 4604 ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY COPYRIGHT AND PROTECTED BY APPLICABLE LAW
